USAGE:

    <stats action="$ACTION"
           stat="$STAT"
           value="$VALUE"

       (o) actor="$ACTOR"
        -  actorRef="$ACTOR_REFERENCE" />


        $ACTION         - The means of altering the stat:
                            ADD: Adds the $VALUE value based on existing
                            DEDUCT: Deducts the $VALUE from the existing amount
                            SET: Overrides existing values and replaces them with $VALUE

        $STAT           - The stat to change. See Actor.Stats enum for values.
        $VALUE          - A numerical value. Random value is allowed:

                          <stats ... value="$RANDOM_NUMBER" randomParams="1-10"> for example


        (o) Optional Fields

        $ACTOR          - The specified actor to perform this action, see ACTOR_REFERENCES
        $ACTOR_REFERENCE- The referred actor (if npc)



